Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

Alex,

Thanks for starting on this. The code is pretty elegant and the simplicity for plug-in developers to add types is nice. It reminds me of a tiny version of some of the Django framework with Horizon. 

I have some comments inline. In addition, here are a few general comments:

Data types for simple properties should be consistent with the json schema types since these are already being used in the metadata definitions catalog.

I do have some concern that this could lead down a path of people needing more powerful validation than just individual properties (the object as a whole).  Some of which could be handled by supporting custom validators, but also could be supplemented or supported by allowing users to supply a json schema that the properties and even the object as a whole are validated against. 

Thanks,
Travis
